## 25.Feb.2020 Met with Tony and got some clairifcation on how to use HISAT2 to index. 




## First, I need to index the red abalone genome
```#!/bin/bash
#SBATCH -D /home/seboles/HISAT2/redabalone_genome/index
#SBATCH -t 100:00:00
#SBATCH -N 1
#SBATCH -n 1
#SBATCH -p high
#SBATCH -c 8
#SBATCH --mem=4G
#SBATCH -J genome_index
module load hisat2/2.1.0
hisat2-build -f /home/seboles/HISAT2/redabalone_genome/halruf.fasta /home/seboles/HISAT2/redabalone_genome/index```


## Then I need to map each to the indexed genome so that I can do tissue specific differential analyses on my concatentated files. 
Male Light Receptor 1. This is to be done in the direcotry containging the concatenated R1 &R2 files.

```#!/bin/bash
#SBATCH -t 48:00:00
#SBATCH -N 1
#SBATCH -n 1
#SBATCH -p high
#SBATCH -c 8
#SBATCH --mem=4G
#SBATCH -J male_light_receptor_1
module load hisat2/2.1.0
module load samtools/1.9
hisat2 --qc-filter -q -x /home/seboles/HISAT2/redabalone_genome_index/index -1 /home/seboles/HISAT2/male/hisat2male/lightreceptor_1_R1.fastq -2 /home/seboles/HISAT2/male/hisat2male/lightreceptor_1_R2.fastq -S lightreceptor_1.sam```





